Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into
2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two #baking trays{} if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @eschalion shallot{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and sliced pepper to the pan.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Stir-fry until the peppers have softened and the chicken is golden all over,
~{6-8%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw
chicken and its packaging.

Add the shallot to the pan and stir-fry until the shallot has softened and the
chicken is cooked, ~{3-4%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no
longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, mix together the garlic, @tomato puree{30%g},
@North Indian style spice mix{1} and half the @mango chutney{80%g}.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir the mixture into the pan until well combined.
Cook until everything begins to caramelise, ~{1%minute}, then remove from the heat.

Pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm
through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Pop the tortillas (3 per person) onto your plates and share out half the
@mayonnaise{2} in the centre of each one. Top with the @pea shoots{40%g} and
mango chutney chicken, then drizzle over the remaining mayo and mango chutney.
Fold over one end to encase the filling and roll up.

Serve with the wedges alongside. Enjoy!

> Step 3 MOD: If you've chosen to get diced chicken breast instead of thigh, cook the recipe
> in the same way.

> These Mango Chutney Curried Diced Chicken Breast Wraps are bursting full of flavours
> and makes the perfect dinner night option from HelloFresh. Cook up a fresh start!